fields.physical_description:
[rugs] Brown, cream, and yellow rug with white fringing. The rug is printed with a diamond shape in the centre and green and pink flowers in a rectangle.
[television] Television with a grey metal stand, cream plastic front and printed paper controls. The screen shows a man water skiing.
[tables (support furniture)] Wooden table with a circular top and foot, stained red.
[chairs] Red wooden chair with round seat and curved back.
[chairs] Red wooden chair with round seat and curved back.
[armchairs] Wooden armchair with red velvet upholstery covering the seat and backrest. The back of the chair has a decorative circular cutout.
[armchairs] Wooden angular armchair covered with bright blue felt fabric. The legs are uncovered.
[sofas] Wooden sofa with red velvet upholstery covering the seat and backrest.
[cushions] Square cushion made from red corduroy.
[tables (support furniture)] Rectangular wooden table.
[dressers (cupboards)] White wooden dresser with bookshelves, drawers and cupboards. The inside of the dresser is painted orange and there is a sunset picture stuck at the back. Two of the cupboards have clear doors and all the handles are made from metal. There is a yellow plastic wine bottle stuck down on the left hand side.
[dolls] Small plastic doll in the form of a man. The figure is dressed in light blue trousers, with a brown belt and gold buckle , black shoes, a brown sleeveless top with a suede effect jacket on top. The doll has flexible limbs so that it can be positioned on furniture in the dolls' house.
[dolls] Small plastic doll in the form of a woman. The figure is dressed in red trousers, a white long sleeved top and a red and white gingham tunic. The doll has flexible limbs so that it can be positioned on furniture in the dolls' house.
[dolls] Small plastic doll in the form of a girl. It is dressed in red shoes, blue jeans and a red and white stripy sweater. The doll has flexible limbs so that it can be positioned on furniture in the dolls' house.
[dolls] Small plastic doll in the form of a boy. The figure is dressed in denim jeans and waistcoat, a light blue shirt, brown shoes and a brown belt with a gold buckle. The doll has flexible limbs so that it can be positioned on furniture in the dolls' house.
[flowerpots] Brown clay flowerpot with green plastic plant which has orange flowers or berries inside.
[flowerpots] Cream plastic flowerpot with a pink flower.
[record player] Orange and siler record player with Lundby on one side.
[globes (cartographic spheres)] A cartographic globe on a gold coloured metal stand. Each country on the globe is coloured in a different colour.
[Dolls' house accessories] Miniature book with paper pages and a dark blue card cover.
[Dolls' house accessories] Miniature paper book with a purple card cover
[Dolls' house accessories] Woven fruit bowl with a green ribbon wrapped around the outside
[Dolls' house accessories] Round orange wrapped in silver foil
[Dolls' house accessories] Red and blue printed record cover containing a red plastic record.

fields.public_access_description:
This unusual house was built by Dr Christopher Cole. Designed as a townhouse the rooms are spread over several floors linked together with several staircases. From the outside the house has a very distinctive appearance with large vertical windows which span three floors. The interior walls can be moved around to create new spaces and the front and side of the house can be opened allowing children (and adults) to play imaginatively with the dolls and furniture inside. 

The house reflects aspects of changing lifestyles at the time, with modern appliances and spacious family rooms. It is furnished with Scandinavian style furniture including a number of pieces by Lundby, Brio and Hanse of Denmark. Lundby started producing dolls’ houses and furniture in 1947 and continue to do so today. The houses and furniture they produced are notable because they reflect the period in which they were made. It was always Lundby’s ambition to keep up with the times, producing houses with electric lighting, and following trends with interior decoration and design.
